  <summary>12/6/1995--Introduced.
Federal Contractor Safety and Health Enforcement Act of 1995 - Amends the Occupational Safety and Health Act to make ineligible for all Federal contracts for a period of three years any person or entity that, with a clear pattern and practice, violates such Act. Allows removal of such debarment or reduction of such period under certain conditions.</summary>
